The symptoms of Dengue include a high fever, severe headache, muscle and joint pain, nausea, vomiting, and a rash that develops on the body. These symptoms can appear within 4-7 days after being infected with the virus. In severe cases, dengue can result in bleeding, low blood pressure, and even death. It is important to consult a doctor and seek medical treatment if you experience these symptoms.

Varicose veins are typically characterized by the appearance of bulging, swollen veins on the legs that may be blue or purple in color. Patients may also experience symptoms such as leg pain, cramping, itching, and aching, especially after prolonged periods of standing or sitting. In advanced cases, the skin around the affected veins may become thickened and discolored, and there may be open sores or ulcers. Some patients may also experience fatigue and heaviness in the legs due to poor circulation.

In serious cases, a drug reaction can cause difficulty breathing, swelling of the face, lips, or tongue, and a rapid heart rate. It is important to seek medical attention if you experience any of these symptoms after taking a new medication.

Additionally, some individuals may experience psychological symptoms such as low self-esteem and depression due to the appearance of their skin.

The symptoms of chicken pox include a red itchy rash, fever, headache, fatigue, loss of appetite, and general discomfort. The rash usually starts on the face, chest, and back and spreads to the rest of the body. The bumps may turn into fluid-filled blisters and eventually scab over. It can also cause flu-like symptoms such as body aches and a mild fever.

Psoriasis is a chronic skin condition that causes red, itchy, and scaly patches on the skin. It is often accompanied by joint pain or stiffness, and in some cases, the skin may also develop small, pitted, or ridged fingernails or toenails. The affected skin may also be prone to cracking, bleeding, and peeling. Other symptoms may include inflammation in the joints, fatigue, and overall discomfort.
